Turkey Got $10 Billion Inflow After Regional Revolts, Zaman Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-06-13T05:35:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/turkey-got-10-billion-inflow-after-regional-revolts-zaman-says.html
About $10.2 billion in deposits from
investors in the  Middle East  and North Africa flowed into  Turkey 
in the first quarter after revolts shook several countries in
the region,  Zaman  reported, citing Turkish central bank
statistics.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 